Wash and dry produce. Halve, peel, and thinly slice half the @red onion{1}; dice remaining half. Cut onion slices in half crosswise. Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Thinly slice @cremini mushrooms{4%ounce} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!).

== Turmeric Rice ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{4%teaspoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @turmeric{1/2%tsp}(1 tsp for 4 servings); cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. (Be sure to measure the turmeric; we sent more.)

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, ¾ cup water, and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil; cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Pickled Onion ==

Meanwhile, in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine sliced onion, @white wine vinegar{2%teaspoon}, @sugar{1/4%tsp}, and a pinch of salt. Cover with #plastic wrap{}; microwave ~{30%seconds}. Set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally.

== Guacamole Sauce ==

In a #second small bowl{}, combine @guacamole{4%tablespoon}, half the cilantro, juice from one lime wedge, a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}, and as much lime zest as you like. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a thick drizzling consistency. Taste and season with salt and @pepper{} if needed.

== Spiced Mushrooms ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms in an even layer and cook, undisturbed, until lightly browned on one side, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: Add another drizzle of oil if pan looks dry.

Add @Mexican spice blend{1%tablespoon}(half the amount; you'll use the rest later), salt, and pepper; cook, stirring occasionally, until mushrooms are browned and crisp, ~{3-4%minutes} more. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

== Garlicky Black Beans ==

Heat a large drizzle of oil in same pan over medium heat. Add @red onion{1}(diced), @garlic powder{1/2%tsp}(half the amount; all for 4 servings), remaining Mexican spice blend, and a big pinch of salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until softened and fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @black beans{1%unit} and their liquid; cook, stirring, until liquid is mostly absorbed and beans are saucy, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Remove from heat; taste and season generously with salt and pepper.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{2}. Top with mushrooms and beans in separate sections. Add pickled onion (draining first) in a pile. Drizzle with guacamole sauce and sprinkle with remaining cilantro. Serve with @blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%ounce} and remaining lime wedges on the side.